article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 64, Texas Wesleyan 60
article.story: SAN ANTONIO, Texas (AP) -- Melvin Smith hit the go-ahead jumper with 24 seconds left and finished with 25 points to help Texas-San Antonio beat Texas Wesleyan 64-60 on Saturday night. Smith scored 18 of his points in the second half, was 12-of-20 from the field and had seven rebounds. Isaiah Allen added 14 points for the Roadrunners (4-6). Nino Etienne's tip-in with 1:16 left gave Texas Wesleyan (7-3) a 58-57 lead until Kurt Attaway's 3-pointer 20 seconds later put the Roadrunners back ahead. Etienne then sank two free throws to tie the score before Smith's jumper from the baseline. C.J. Higginbotham led Texas Wesleyan with 16 points, including four 3-pointers. Kevin Williams added 12 points and had 10 rebounds.
